They emit light.

00:24:41.820 --> 00:24:43.920
The light goes through
an optical fiber.

00:24:43.920 --> 00:24:46.930
And now, after
the beam splitter,

00:24:46.930 --> 00:24:48.940
when you detect one
photon you don't

00:24:48.940 --> 00:24:50.730
know which ion has
emitted the photon.

00:24:56.330 --> 00:25:01.760
So this is exactly the
setup which I described.

00:25:04.570 --> 00:25:09.990
Of course, in an
optical fiber you

00:25:09.990 --> 00:25:15.540
have the two good polarizations
are horizontal and vertical

00:25:15.540 --> 00:25:18.120
in the polarization
maintaining fiber.

00:25:18.120 --> 00:25:20.710
So therefore, the
light which originally

00:25:20.710 --> 00:25:23.840
was emitted in a circular base
is-- angular momentum selection

00:25:23.840 --> 00:25:26.324
rules-- transformed into
linearly polarized light

00:25:26.324 --> 00:25:27.240
using the [INAUDIBLE].

