00:26:31.470 --> 00:26:34.740
have a superposition state of
photon in one polarization--

00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:39.600
let's say a sigma plus photon
going to a magnetic quantum

00:26:39.600 --> 00:26:41.890
number state m equals
plus 1 and a sigma

00:26:41.890 --> 00:26:44.360
minus photon going
to m equals minus 1.

00:26:44.360 --> 00:26:48.060
And this is a pure state.

00:26:48.060 --> 00:26:52.620
The mixture only comes
if you're not careful.

00:26:52.620 --> 00:26:54.120
If you have a
magnetic field and you

00:26:54.120 --> 00:26:55.930
don't shield your
magnetic field well,

00:26:55.930 --> 00:26:58.580
or you have some
magnetized materials

00:26:58.580 --> 00:27:00.520
and you were not
aware of it, then that

00:27:00.520 --> 00:27:04.360
means that you get
different phase shifts which

00:27:04.360 --> 00:27:08.090
you can't calculate for, so
now you have a random phase.

00:27:08.090 --> 00:27:11.120
You don't know it, and
if you have ignorance

00:27:11.120 --> 00:27:13.960
you have to trace out or you
have to average over the phase.

00:27:13.960 --> 00:27:17.210
And then your pure state
becomes a density matrix.

00:27:17.210 --> 00:27:19.365
But the quantum
mechanical process itself

00:27:19.365 --> 00:27:23.720
of a particle having
different branching ratios

00:27:23.720 --> 00:27:25.710
is a pure system.

00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:28.280
It undergoes unitary
time evolution,

00:27:28.280 --> 00:27:30.930
and it stays in a pure state.

00:27:30.930 --> 00:27:37.700
And the state which is
populated by two ions, both

00:27:37.700 --> 00:27:41.330
