00:29:23.060 --> 00:29:27.200
OK I've used the word
Bell, Bell states

00:29:27.200 --> 00:29:31.710
so often, I think it's time
to talk about what Mr. Bell is

00:29:31.710 --> 00:29:34.225
famous for, namely
the Bell's Inequality.

00:29:39.150 --> 00:29:43.730
So I said already
in the introduction

00:29:43.730 --> 00:29:48.460
for the quantumness of
light and entanglement

00:29:48.460 --> 00:29:53.910
that it is the EPR Paradox
in the Bell's inequalities

00:29:53.910 --> 00:29:56.970
which a lot of people,
including myself, think

00:29:56.970 --> 00:29:59.250
is the deeper essence
of quantum physics.

00:29:59.250 --> 00:30:05.000
It really shows that
quantum physics is not just

00:30:05.000 --> 00:30:07.100
classical physics
with wave character,

00:30:07.100 --> 00:30:10.080
it goes way beyond it.

00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:15.140
So I want to demonstrate
that with Bell's inequality.

00:30:15.140 --> 00:30:18.370
And the formulation
which is very simple,

00:30:18.370 --> 00:30:20.800
and I want to present it
here, is an inequality,

00:30:20.800 --> 00:30:22.560
which is-- I mean the name.

00:30:22.560 --> 00:30:26.420
Many Bell's inequalities now,
you have different states,

00:30:26.420 --> 00:30:29.860
different detectors, and you
can derive Bell's inequalities

00:30:29.860 --> 00:30:33.000
which are then violated
by quantum physics.

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:37.120
And what I want to present
here is the CHSH inequality.

00:30:37.120 --> 00:30:44.860
That's Clauser,
Horn, Shimony, and--

00:30:44.860 --> 00:30:46.150
